<TITLE> BFF decides Super Cup grouping </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 18 (bdnews24.com)  The Bangladesh Football Federation on Wednesday has decided in principle that the groping of the newly-installed Super Cup would follow the standing of the top eight finishers of the just concluded B League. The teams occupying uneven places have been put into Group A while even teams placed in Group B. That means champions Abahani Limited, third-placed Sheikh Russel KC, fifth-placed Chittagong Mohammedan SC and seventh-placed Rahmatganj MFS have been kept in Group A while Group B comprises runners-up Mohammedan SC, fourth-placed Brothers Union, sixth-placed Farashganj SC and eighth-placed Chittagong Abahani Limited. Tournament committee co-chairman Shawkat Ali Khan Jahangir said that they would follow other formats if there was any objection. It had earlier decided that the champions would get Tk one crore while the runners-up will receive Tk 25 lakh. Besides, the third finishers will receive Tk 7 lakh, fourth finishers Tk 5 lakh, fifth finishers Tk 4 lakh, sixth finishers Tk 3 lakh and seventh and eighth finishers Tk 2 lakh each. Jahangir said that the two top teams from each group would play in the double-leg semi-finals while two bottom finishers from each group in a single-semi-final to decide the positions. The tournament committee also decided that the teams could sign up to five foreign players, but could play four in a match. bd
